Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.10,0:00:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about serenity. Serenity that arises then is an automatic consequence of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.50,0:01:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding and comprehension. It's affirmative, simplistic, non-operative, and people, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,invitational, invitational, no promotion, no promotion. It's non-predictive because
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.54,0:01:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,reality is non-linear and you cannot tell what the secret is now. Why would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.68,0:01:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it you can't tell the future? There'd be no point to existence, human existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.82,0:01:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because the future then is created by every choice and every option you make, is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.32,0:01:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it not? Every choice and option determines where you are within the overall infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.79,0:01:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,field. Because the future hasn't happened yet, it has no reality, and you can't calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.50,0:01:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.20,0:02:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that is not a reality, you know, is a fiction. So there's fictional propositions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.35,0:02:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,about the future, but the future obviously is not a possibility or there would be no
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.62,0:02:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,point to creation, no point to divinity or existence, much less human life, yeah? Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.50,0:02:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying? It's only because you have an option, you could choose
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.19,0:02:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this or that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.19,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.36,0:02:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if this, the outcome was determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.50,0:02:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There'd be no point to human life, would there? We'd all be in some other realm where
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.87,0:02:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you're done already. And if you blew it, you blew it forever. If you blew it, boy, you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.03,0:02:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,blew it, okay. It's not sentimental. We said, you know, the value of being empathic, I know
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is to walk in my brother's moccasins. That's empathy. That's coming from the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.03,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of humanity within you. Your heart understands where their heart is. So I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.65,0:03:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.74,0:03:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.84,0:03:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.93,0:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.00,0:03:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.06,0:03:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.08,0:03:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:03:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.13,0:03:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.19,0:03:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.24,0:03:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.30,0:03:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.37,0:03:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.47,0:03:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.75,0:03:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.81,0:03:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand how they feel. Sympathy is joining them, which is something else. As a psychiatrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you're empathic, but you won't last long if you're sympathetic. Sympathetic. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.74,0:03:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.50,0:03:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the amateur offers sympathy, which is a way of seduction. Sympathy is a form of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.81,0:03:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,seduction and exploitation. Empathy allows you both to maintain your own integrity. I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.65,0:03:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-sentimental, non-authoritarian, no rules. Teachers are respected but don't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.90,0:03:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,walk around with special titles. Educational, provides information so it's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.68,0:03:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily educative and inspiration. It's self-supporting, it's freestanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.68,0:04:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,devoid of induced or altered states of consciousness, which is something else I
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.37,0:04:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,just got through writing about. Repetitious things, exercises, physical
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.65,0:04:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and otherwise, can induce an altered state of consciousness. Biofeedback,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,alpha-wave training, various things, can provide an altered state of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness, but that is not a spiritual condition. The altered state of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.02,0:04:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness then disappears when you remove the basis. Certain spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.31,0:04:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,disciplines,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.31,0:04:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,through repetitive practices, bring about states of satori, but then when the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.42,0:04:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,exercise is over and you get up and you walk around, the state disappears. The state
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.45,0:05:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears. A prevailing level of consciousness is not dependent on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,externals, much less physical physicality or physical manipulations. We said that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.60,0:05:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,brain function is the automatic consequence of that which
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.35,0:05:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you have become. The so-called cities, supernormal phenomena, are the automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.62,0:05:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of that which you have become. So to take classes on learning how
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.82,0:05:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to fly or bi-locate or anything like that, you can see, are actually injurious. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.74,0:05:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the spiritual ego is what seeks them out. Why do you want to learn to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.77,0:05:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,travel and fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously the spiritual ego gives some kind of status to that. Some kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:06:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,status. See? People who seriously do the, you know, spiritual work eventually reach
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.07,0:06:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a state where these phenomena appear of their own. You hold it in mind and of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.39,0:06:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,course it shows up. You drive into the Lincoln Center in New York City and you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.93,0:06:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,hold in mind a parking space right near Lincoln Center. By God, the closest one is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.37,0:06:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,there. You pull up, the other car pulls apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.05,0:06:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the first, those begin to happen, you call them miraculous. After a while you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.14,0:06:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,just see it's normal. It's just normal. What you're holding in mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.50,0:06:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,manifesting when conditions are favorable. To seek the cities or so-called
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.60,0:06:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,mystical powers for their own is off the rail to begin with. The very reason it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,can't work because the reason you want it in the first place is already
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.02,0:06:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You want it from the viewpoint of spiritual pride. Why do you want to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.87,0:07:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to fly? Tell me that, please. If you were meant to fly, you'd have wings, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.49,0:07:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're meant to walk, pedestrian. As a pedestrian, you keep humility. If you gave
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.75,0:07:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,men wings, his ego's bad enough as it is, I mean, he'd really go nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.94,0:07:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we'll move past that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.82,0:07:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we want to get to the dualities of attraction and aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.62,0:07:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because these apply to all the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.57,0:07:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All the levels of consciousness are held in place by what I call, the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.25,0:07:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,juice of the payoff. You're getting a payoff, and you look at
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.58,0:07:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go of it in a negative way, so you develop an aversion. Every
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,positionality that your mind gets caught in is attracted there by an attraction,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.42,0:07:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's held there also by an aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to be forgiven. How often
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:07:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,have we heard that? I forgive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.86,0:08:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,him, but he doesn't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.80,0:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.44,0:08:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,him, but he doesn't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.37,0:08:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all the veterans of World War II long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving their
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.02,0:08:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,former enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but I heard there was one guy, a holdout
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,on television not long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.56,0:08:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though it's been over 60
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.08,0:08:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,years or whatever, this guy was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.93,0:08:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,holding on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding on,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.75,0:08:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,holding on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't deserve to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.08,0:08:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiven. Who's the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.87,0:08:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,beneficiary of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.15,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiveness? Not the person
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you forgive, but the forgivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.10,0:08:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's denying himself
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.77,0:08:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the benefit of forgiveness. He's not
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.03,0:08:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,denying the other guy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.44,0:08:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.25,0:08:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The warrior of both
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.03,0:08:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,sides, in my view, were equally
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.03,0:08:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous. They both did what they thought
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.13,0:09:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was required by their
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.50,0:09:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,role in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.29,0:09:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,By their obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.32,0:09:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to God, government,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.63,0:09:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,womanhood, their mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.63,0:09:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and God knows what all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.05,0:09:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody did what they felt they needed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.41,0:09:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to do to fulfill that role
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.41,0:09:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I always saw
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.89,0:09:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone equally
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.34,0:09:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous, no matter which side they're on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctors Without Borders
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.48,0:09:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,sees it the same way. They don't care
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.53,0:09:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which side they're on. If they come
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.53,0:09:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in injured, you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.50,0:09:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,repair his leg. It doesn't matter which
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.51,0:09:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,side he was on. Because
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.55,0:09:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,each side is doing what they consider to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.67,0:09:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest good. So
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.55,0:09:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the attraction, then, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.46,0:09:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the aversion. These
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.94,0:09:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are general. When we get to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.22,0:09:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the levels, we'll be more specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.96,0:09:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But generally, to see
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.24,0:09:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what holds things in mind gives you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.37,0:09:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,tools by which to undo
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.37,0:09:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,them. First of all, we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.40,0:09:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,like that which is familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.37,0:10:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd rather be wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time because it's comfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.66,0:10:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And to find a new
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.76,0:10:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,way home. Did you ever try a new way home from
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.69,0:10:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,work? It's annoying. I've tried
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.44,0:10:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, this is boring. I'm going to try a different way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.76,0:10:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon, I'm going back the same
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.25,0:10:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,old way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.11,0:10:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We like the familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.28,0:10:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Habitual. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,don't like really
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.36,0:10:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,change and fear the newer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,unless we choose it. And then we choose it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.46,0:10:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for novelty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.40,0:10:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So this way, the attraction is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.45,0:10:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easier
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.38,0:10:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to just hate the SOB
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.57,0:10:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,than it is to go through the effort
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.49,0:10:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of processing it and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.38,0:10:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving. The attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.49,0:10:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of pride then,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.47,0:10:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so we have pride in all of our positionalities
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.90,0:10:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the aversion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.57,0:10:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.73,0:10:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,People confuse humility with
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,humiliation. The truly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.33,0:10:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,humble person cannot be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.95,0:10:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,humiliated. The person
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.46,0:11:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who owns his downside
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.17,0:11:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.58,0:11:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is not sensitive about slights.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.73,0:11:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't feel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.54,0:11:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that their rights have been violated
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because somebody disagrees with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because they've accepted their downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.54,0:11:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get over being
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.27,0:11:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,sensitive, that's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.27,0:11:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If your feelings get hurt easily, sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.27,0:11:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and make a list of all the downsides
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.27,0:11:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of your self you can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.27,0:11:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then picture the great comedians
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.27,0:11:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of all time discussing
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.27,0:11:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,your problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.27,0:11:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,great therapists of Jack Benny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.27,0:11:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the great Red Skelton. Those are the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.27,0:11:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,great therapists. And the black
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.27,0:11:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,guy who did more to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.27,0:11:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,get rid of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.27,0:11:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,prejudice against blacks. The guy who blew himself
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.27,0:11:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,up with something. Richard Friar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.27,0:11:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard Friar, yeah. By the time he knocked
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,out all those stereotypes, there wasn't anything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.27,0:11:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,left you could say about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.44,0:11:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do the same thing with yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.44,0:11:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.52,0:11:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody can hurt you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.91,0:12:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You accept all the things that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.91,0:12:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,embarrassed about which hadn't happened
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.91,0:12:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and accept that that's part
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.91,0:12:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of your karmic inheritance
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.91,0:12:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to have lived through those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.91,0:12:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And now nobody can
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.91,0:12:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,hurt you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.11,0:12:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So pride
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.87,0:12:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,keeps us away from humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.87,0:12:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the humble
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,person whose feelings cannot be hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.87,0:12:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Feelings cannot be hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.28,0:12:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you call yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.87,0:12:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I love nicknames amongst, this is understood
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.87,0:12:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst men,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have nicknames for each other
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.87,0:12:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which emphasize their surety.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.87,0:12:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That was called surety in the Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.87,0:12:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well nowadays a sensitive person
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.25,0:12:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,would be, their rights are violated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.25,0:12:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,they've been,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.25,0:12:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,not supposed to be discrimination
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.25,0:12:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,based on height, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.73,0:12:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Surety. So anyway, you own
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.73,0:12:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and amongst the work
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.88,0:12:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,crew we always used ethnic
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.88,0:12:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,names for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:12:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in Wisconsin there were Bohonks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.88,0:13:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and Germans, you know, we all had
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,names for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.91,0:13:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was Jigaboos and Bohonks
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.91,0:13:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.12,0:13:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we all owned that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.12,0:13:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore it was a fun thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.12,0:13:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.55,0:13:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiss me I'm Polish, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.55,0:13:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the guy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.55,0:13:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who used to go over to the girl's ranch every
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.55,0:13:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,month and he had his license plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.55,0:13:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiss me I'm Polish. Instantly you love all the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.55,0:13:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Polish people and you really always feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.55,0:13:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,kissing them, you know, because
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.55,0:13:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes you out of the stereotype
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.55,0:13:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and into the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.69,0:13:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.85,0:13:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Confusion of anger with strength
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.85,0:13:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and passivity as weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.85,0:13:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to give up anger
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.85,0:13:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because people swell up with anger
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.85,0:13:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,get an artificial feeling of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.85,0:13:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger gives you an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.33,0:13:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,artificial charge like you are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.33,0:13:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,stronger than you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.39,0:13:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel stronger
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.39,0:13:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually you're not because the angry
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.39,0:13:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,person of course is much weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And in, you know, karate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.39,0:14:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and various martial arts
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.39,0:14:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and various
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.39,0:14:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,other things I've done
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you try to provoke the guy to get mad
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.39,0:14:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because once he gets mad you got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.39,0:14:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.64,0:14:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You got him. The minute you got him mad
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.64,0:14:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he freezes into an angry
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.64,0:14:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.15,0:14:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly you got him. In a flash
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.15,0:14:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the angry person is skewered
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.15,0:14:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,on the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.23,0:14:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction of course is always
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.23,0:14:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to win and never to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.23,0:14:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but winning and losing are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.23,0:14:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,how you contextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.23,0:14:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego's loss is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.28,0:14:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,usually the spirit's gain and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.28,0:14:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.32,0:14:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is always importance and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.32,0:14:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of being a nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.45,0:14:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is always seeking a gain
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.45,0:14:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,wants money
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.45,0:14:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,wants excitement
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.58,0:14:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and serenity is the last thing it wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.58,0:14:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Teenagers see
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.84,0:14:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,serenity as boredom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:14:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing happening around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.84,0:14:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean what's happening here in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.84,0:15:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean everybody just goes to work and goes to church
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.84,0:15:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on Sunday. I mean what's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I want to meditate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.21,0:15:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and think about nothing, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.21,0:15:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.39,0:15:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,loves excitement and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,hates serenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.39,0:15:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates boredom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.65,0:15:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's addicted to desiring, wanting
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it loves status
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.65,0:15:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,hates the idea of being a nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.65,0:15:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wants to be noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.65,0:15:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course the Hollywood
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,madness is the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.65,0:15:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,desire to be noticed at
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.65,0:15:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,all costs, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.65,0:15:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.78,0:15:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,opinionated, doesn't want to be seen as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.78,0:15:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ordinary. It's just awful
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.78,0:15:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to be ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.33,0:15:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the safety of being ordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't wait to be ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know anybody ordinary who was
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,assassinated lately? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.20,0:15:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to blow off the bus or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.58,0:16:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To have an opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.60,0:16:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you then, so
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.60,0:16:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,this is why we need freedom from speech
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.60,0:16:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we have an inversion of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.60,0:16:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual values in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.60,0:16:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in which freedom of speech
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.91,0:16:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,has become worshipped as the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,ideal pinnacle of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.91,0:16:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. The pinnacle
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.96,0:16:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of this country and all we stand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.96,0:16:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for is called free speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.11,0:16:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.11,0:16:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget two-fifths or something like that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.11,0:16:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.00,0:16:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth, higher
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.23,0:16:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,than reason, higher than logic
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.23,0:16:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.76,0:16:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than sanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.70,0:16:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.45,0:16:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,God. It feeds the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.91,0:16:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,media. The media is in a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.62,0:16:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,feeding frenzy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.62,0:17:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,over free speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.25,0:17:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism to the max is what
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it amounts to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism to the max.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.25,0:17:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is more important
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,than God. Free
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.16,0:17:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,speech. Calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.67,0:17:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it's one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.67,0:17:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,attributes of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.40,0:17:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,political freedom but it is not
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.40,0:17:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest good of all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.40,0:17:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it gives equal
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.49,0:17:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,voice to fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.49,0:17:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it not? Equal voice
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.91,0:17:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to fallacy. When it's time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.55,0:17:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to operate and do brain surgery
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.55,0:17:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't pull the people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.17,0:17:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,around for their opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy should
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.20,0:17:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you think I should
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.20,0:17:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,clamp the left
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,cerebral artery?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All in favor? Now they want
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.85,0:17:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a family in the operating room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.88,0:18:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I would refuse to operate on anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.88,0:18:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with a family in the operating room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.98,0:18:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to document it so you can be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sued later if you make a wrong move.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.98,0:18:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean the intention is so
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.98,0:18:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integers to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't vote
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.77,0:18:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on truth, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.77,0:18:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't vote on truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And the downside of our society
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, which if not corrected
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.20,0:18:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,will be its destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.20,0:18:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,much as Socrates predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.20,0:18:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in 350 BC or 450
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.20,0:18:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,please don't write me it was 458
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.20,0:18:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not 350.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Around that time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.43,0:18:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,he said if you give every man an equal vote
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and equal power he will destroy society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So free
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,speech then. So
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.46,0:18:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say now for history.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.46,0:18:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For historical reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.80,0:18:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That the downside
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.74,0:18:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of this society occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.74,0:18:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,when action was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.74,0:19:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,legislated
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.31,0:19:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from the bench as
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,symbolic speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.63,0:19:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If action is symbolic speech
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in a free country you can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.49,0:19:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,say anything you want
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.49,0:19:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no constraint at all
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.49,0:19:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,on anything by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.49,0:19:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do anything I want
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.67,0:19:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so if I want to publicly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.85,0:19:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,burn the flag
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.46,0:19:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is that speech? I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.16,0:19:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,even open my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.92,0:19:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's symbolic speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.00,0:19:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the Ku Klux Klan
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.00,0:19:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is okay. Therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.05,0:19:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sodomy is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.56,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter Philly is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.56,0:19:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all symbolic speech are they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.56,0:19:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All action now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.24,0:19:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is free of all restraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.24,0:19:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.33,0:20:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,answerability, no responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.33,0:20:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The complete and total destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.40,0:20:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of morality and ethics without which
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.40,0:20:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,society soon becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.40,0:20:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.88,0:20:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It will become the Chomsky ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.91,0:20:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Atheistic
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.53,0:20:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.99,0:20:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside then is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.99,0:20:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.99,0:20:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who believe in no government
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.26,0:20:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anarchists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.75,0:20:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you call them. Anarchists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The anarchists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the atheistic anarchist
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.75,0:20:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will come about through relativism
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.75,0:20:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by which
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.82,0:20:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,anything I do is my
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,right to do
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.82,0:20:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's my right
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.82,0:20:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's symbolic speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.30,0:20:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.88,0:20:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just symbolic speech folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:21:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,With a little sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.64,0:21:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore with no right or wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.64,0:21:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then war is just as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.64,0:21:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,okay as peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.64,0:21:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality is just as okay as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.64,0:21:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,law abiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to truth because
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.04,0:21:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy is of equal
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.04,0:21:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.30,0:21:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So historically
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we say it for the record
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.35,0:21:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.35,0:21:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,civilization came about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.83,0:21:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,when action was
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.86,0:21:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,legally defined
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.19,0:21:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as symbolic speech
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.19,0:21:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,without restraints, responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.19,0:21:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or answerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.53,0:21:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If that don't take down a society
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.53,0:21:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.56,0:21:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what would.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.56,0:21:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can you have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.64,0:21:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.64,0:21:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with such a prospect perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.64,0:21:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've said the worst thing I can
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.64,0:21:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about the world, I've already said
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.64,0:22:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the worst thing I can say about the world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.47,0:22:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because through acceptance then you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.47,0:22:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,accept that is the karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.47,0:22:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality of humankind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're not here to question
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.55,0:22:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God's purpose in creating human life
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.55,0:22:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.60,0:22:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody wants to change the world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,remember Ramana Maharshi said
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.05,0:22:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,there's several ways
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.05,0:22:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.05,0:22:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you can ask who am I constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.05,0:22:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for you know
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.05,0:22:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,20 years constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.22,0:22:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you spend a whole lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,asking who am I
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.59,0:22:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and spend a whole lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.73,0:22:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can surrender the world to God
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.79,0:22:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and you got it in a second
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.79,0:22:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want everybody to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.79,0:22:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the world to God at lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.07,0:22:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll resume at what time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.22,0:22:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we will resume at 2 o'clock
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.22,0:22:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're going to spend more time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.22,0:23:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,on questions than answers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.68,0:23:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was spoiled by being in Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.51,0:23:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,went there twice
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.90,0:23:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,important missions
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.34,0:23:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,society is this way
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.34,0:23:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when they meet each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.34,0:23:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all the people wait on you in the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.53,0:23:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.53,0:23:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you know and you get spoiled by it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.75,0:23:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the politeness, the reverence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.75,0:23:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for something higher than your personal ego
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.75,0:23:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a charming
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.92,0:23:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,charming society
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.92,0:23:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.27,0:23:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.27,0:23:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.14,0:23:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to further clarify
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.14,0:23:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.14,0:23:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,like everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.35,0:23:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.35,0:23:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it was first discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.80,0:23:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this particular usage
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.80,0:24:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,actually my own observations
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.80,0:24:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the 70s
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.94,0:24:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a lecture by
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.94,0:24:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,John Diamond
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.94,0:24:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I was going to give
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.94,0:24:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to give demonstrations of it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.94,0:24:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.93,0:24:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed a subject
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.93,0:24:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.27,0:24:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I grabbed some
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.27,0:24:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we had the second attitudinal healing center
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.27,0:24:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerry Jempolski
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.27,0:24:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,came to New York
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.27,0:24:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,stayed with us this weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.27,0:24:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with his staff
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.27,0:24:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we started an attitudinal healing center
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.27,0:24:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had an active Course in Miracles group
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.27,0:24:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that met in the clinic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.27,0:24:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for intractable
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.27,0:24:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,incurable conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.50,0:24:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.50,0:24:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I grabbed a couple of people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.01,0:24:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to be
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.47,0:24:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to work with me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.47,0:24:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.63,0:24:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and certain things make everybody go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.63,0:24:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,fluorescent lights
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.63,0:24:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sweet and low held over the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.63,0:24:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,pesticides
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.66,0:25:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,held over the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.66,0:25:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,made everybody go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.66,0:25:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so I said
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.66,0:25:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a couple of volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.66,0:25:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I'll go with you tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.66,0:25:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so I said well try it out
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.66,0:25:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I did the fluorescent light and he didn't go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.43,0:25:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I did the sweet and low he didn't go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.43,0:25:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I did the pesticides he didn't go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.51,0:25:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I said what the world is this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.51,0:25:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody goes weak from these things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.51,0:25:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but these people didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.77,0:25:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,wow
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.91,0:25:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so then we did an investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.91,0:25:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we had some people just starting the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.91,0:25:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and we tested them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.91,0:25:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and they went weak
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.25,0:25:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with the same things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.31,0:25:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,then we tested them a couple of months later
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.31,0:25:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it no longer made them go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.31,0:25:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we found that after
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.41,0:25:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,about less than 75
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.41,0:25:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,around in there
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.41,0:25:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,if a person stayed with the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.41,0:25:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time they got that far
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.41,0:25:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they were only subject to what you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.41,0:25:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is less than 70 I think
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.41,0:25:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only subject to what you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.41,0:26:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,if you believe you got a fever
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.41,0:26:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you got it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.41,0:26:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,just the fact that you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.41,0:26:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,believe and think that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.41,0:26:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,gives it the power over you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.41,0:26:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.41,0:26:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the beginning of calibrating levels
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.41,0:26:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.41,0:26:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.66,0:26:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology is also
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.20,0:26:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in its infancy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.20,0:26:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we're just discovering
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.61,0:26:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we discovered something
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.61,0:26:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,discrepancies which came up at London
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.61,0:26:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,lunch today
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.68,0:26:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that we didn't know before
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.68,0:26:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just want you to demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.68,0:26:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,how it's evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.03,0:26:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we discovered that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.05,0:26:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the application
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.05,0:26:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you see when we calibrate things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.05,0:26:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the Heisenberg principle is operative
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.05,0:26:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we have just observed something
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.05,0:26:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,asked a question that's never been asked before
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.05,0:26:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of history
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.27,0:26:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and by doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.27,0:26:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we discovered we already
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.27,0:26:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are changing the calibrated levels of things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.04,0:27:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,people over 200 when you witness and observe
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.04,0:27:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,something from lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.04,0:27:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are already raising its calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.04,0:27:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.04,0:27:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,measurably
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.69,0:27:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so we found things that we considered
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.69,0:27:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,adorable
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.72,0:27:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fact that you consider it adorable
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.72,0:27:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it would have been a 204
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.72,0:27:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it will jump to 310 or something
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.72,0:27:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,independently
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.78,0:27:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and that same
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.78,0:27:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,manifestation will be
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.78,0:27:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnosable by everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.78,0:27:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.43,0:27:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a fact to resist
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.43,0:27:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,wow
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.43,0:27:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so don't you see what this means
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.48,0:27:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your lovingness by witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.48,0:27:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,see when I say
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.48,0:27:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to go to fancy things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.48,0:27:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,just witness the sacredness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.48,0:27:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.31,0:27:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,approach all of love with reverence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.31,0:27:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and good will
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.73,0:27:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and by doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.85,0:28:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're changing the world
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.35,0:28:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.35,0:28:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so if we say
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.58,0:28:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitty's Purr is adorable and loving
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.58,0:28:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if Kitty's Purr was at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.58,0:28:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,before we said it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.72,0:28:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,probably not
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.72,0:28:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.72,0:28:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.78,0:28:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.78,0:28:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the sheer observation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.78,0:28:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the higher the level of consciousness of the observer
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.78,0:28:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater the impact on the observed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.84,0:28:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have literally been changing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.84,0:28:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.84,0:28:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and much of society by the sheer observation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.84,0:28:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of the work that we're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.84,0:28:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,collectively
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.07,0:28:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that something
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.07,0:28:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so everything we look at lovingly
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.35,0:28:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,huh
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.23,0:28:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.25,0:28:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see how the Komodo dragon is making out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.25,0:28:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,well
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.80,0:28:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.74,0:28:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,he's just being what he is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.74,0:29:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless him
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.74,0:29:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,he's just being what he is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.74,0:29:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,being a good Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.25,0:29:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of course you eat everything up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.17,0:29:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Komodo dragon did calibrate at 40
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.91,0:29:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the adorable Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.91,0:29:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 45
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.91,0:29:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,48
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.42,0:29:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,47
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.54,0:29:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,48
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.54,0:29:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing the lovability of the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.54,0:29:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is an expression of divinity's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.54,0:29:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,unfoldment of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.54,0:29:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so as we witness the unfoldment of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.54,0:29:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and acknowledge that his source
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.54,0:29:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.54,0:29:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we're already raising the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.54,0:29:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,all that is within this world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.54,0:29:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,wow
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.44,0:29:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so this world is becoming
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.59,0:29:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that which we hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.59,0:29:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,just wow hmm
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.59,0:29:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,look at all the power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.72,0:29:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he walked around and didn't know it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.72,0:29:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.16,0:29:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so everything that we look at
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.16,0:30:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive it for being what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.16,0:30:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,witness the sacredness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.16,0:30:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is an expression of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.25,0:30:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.25,0:30:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,at some level of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.25,0:30:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and it serves some ultimate purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.90,0:30:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so we stop hating it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.90,0:30:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and see its intrinsic beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.93,0:30:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.93,0:30:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is an impressive animal
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.93,0:30:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,impressive you know
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.93,0:30:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where this came from
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.93,0:30:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,last night we were watching alligators
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.93,0:30:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we love the nature channel
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.79,0:30:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want to learn a lot about spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.79,0:30:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you just watch the nature channel
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.79,0:30:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.79,0:30:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you see in nature
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.79,0:30:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,where you don't have any prejudices
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.79,0:30:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the witnessing of phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.79,0:30:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that you won't see in humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.85,0:30:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because you got too many
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.85,0:30:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,upsides and downsides
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.85,0:30:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was marvelous
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.85,0:30:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,here's the hippopotamus and the alligators
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.85,0:30:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the alligators
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.89,0:30:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,are on the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.89,0:30:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hippopotamus is also on the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.89,0:30:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but the hippopotamus
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.89,0:31:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,has sort of a maternal motherly instinct
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.89,0:31:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,towards alligators
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.89,0:31:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean who could love an alligator but a hippopotamus
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.89,0:31:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,now that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.08,0:31:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody is afraid of alligators
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.08,0:31:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,except hippopotamus
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.08,0:31:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,hippopotamus comes over and nudges the alligator
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.08,0:31:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and often even licks him
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.67,0:31:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes sure that the alligator is comfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.67,0:31:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the alligator is twitching
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.67,0:31:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hippo will push the alligator over
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.67,0:31:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,until the alligator is happy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.67,0:31:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so here's the alligators all happy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.67,0:31:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the hippopotamus is like tending to them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.67,0:31:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all like mothers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.67,0:31:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,overlooking the babies here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.67,0:31:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and nudging them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.67,0:31:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine licking an alligator
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.31,0:31:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,now there's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.31,0:31:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,love and acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.31,0:31:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so the hippos
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.31,0:31:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,love the alligators and nurture them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.31,0:31:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and lick them and protect them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.31,0:32:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and see to their comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.31,0:32:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that marvelous
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.39,0:32:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's certainly marvelous
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.39,0:32:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't see that on the nature channel
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.39,0:32:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you see you won't read that in the New York Times
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.39,0:32:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so we should be more like the hippopotamus
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.45,0:32:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.48,0:32:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and be sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.48,0:32:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,nurturing towards
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.48,0:32:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all that the world really looks down at
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.48,0:32:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.48,0:32:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,homo horribilis
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.48,0:32:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll start fretting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.21,0:32:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,whether Ben Loudon is getting a sunburn
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.21,0:32:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,getting sand in his eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.21,0:32:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from the wind out there
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.21,0:32:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.32,0:32:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that he does what he feels
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.32,0:32:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it is his destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.46,0:32:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to do
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.46,0:32:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.72,0:32:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of Socrates
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.88,0:32:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he does what he feels obligated
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.88,0:33:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to do
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.94,0:33:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.94,0:33:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,like a hippopotamus
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.94,0:33:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we should make sure he feels comfy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.00,0:33:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in his pillows
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.00,0:33:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.07,0:33:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but isn't that amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.18,0:33:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.18,0:33:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the discrepancies
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.18,0:33:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because this work covers some years
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.18,0:33:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and truth versus false
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.18,0:33:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so those calibrations were done
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.18,0:33:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,all from 2003
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.18,0:33:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,right up to the beginning of 2005
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.18,0:33:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and some of them changed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.18,0:33:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as merely the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.18,0:33:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of our having calibrated them
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.18,0:33:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,without our realizing that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.27,0:33:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,okay so we just got today at lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.27,0:33:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what was about
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.27,0:33:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.27,0:33:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.36,0:33:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,man's desire to know the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.36,0:33:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to pull the truth to him
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.36,0:33:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because this was just a realization
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.36,0:33:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't any thinking about it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.36,0:33:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it was just suddenly you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.55,0:33:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,wow
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.55,0:33:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.55,0:34:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on who's doing the observing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.55,0:34:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so the more loving the person
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.55,0:34:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.66,0:34:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in a certain way
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.66,0:34:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,has a powerful tendency
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.65,0:34:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to have potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.65,0:34:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's one of the mechanisms
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.65,0:34:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by which
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.82,0:34:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution unfolds
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.82,0:34:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as creation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.82,0:34:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so creation is continuous
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.82,0:34:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it happened today at lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.92,0:34:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there was creation right there
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.92,0:34:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.92,0:34:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there's creation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.11,0:34:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,gotcha
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.11,0:34:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so thank you Susie
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.55,0:34:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,without Susie I wouldn't know these things
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.55,0:34:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just puzzle over them
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.09,0:34:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to find a hippopotamus
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.09,0:34:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to work with
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.09,0:34:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a friendly hippo
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.09,0:34:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,probably because
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.09,0:34:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a hippo if you hold something in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.09,0:34:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in a certain way
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.09,0:34:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,he probably reacts one way
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.09,0:34:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if you hold something else in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.63,0:34:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he reacts a different way
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.63,0:35:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's yes and that's no
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.76,0:35:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,their mouths are just amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.84,0:35:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,even alligators are scared of hippos
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.84,0:35:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,even alligators
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.84,0:35:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and they kill more people
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.84,0:35:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,than any other animal on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.84,0:35:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet they're the most
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.84,0:35:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,benign creature when you see it around
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.84,0:35:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,how could a hippo have a maternal
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.57,0:35:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,instinct towards an alligator
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.57,0:35:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway they apparently made friends
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.92,0:35:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,over the millennia
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.92,0:35:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,ok so where were we with the slides
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.92,0:35:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.34,0:35:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to do more
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.34,0:35:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneous interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.34,0:35:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.34,0:35:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just talking to Robert about it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.34,0:35:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,who's our mastermind genius
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.34,0:35:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,behind all the productions
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.34,0:35:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll work out a way
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.34,0:35:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to sort of wander through the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.34,0:35:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've done that in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.34,0:35:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody's sort of liked that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.34,0:35:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can talk to the person
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.34,0:35:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and they come up with what's real to them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.11,0:35:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.11,0:35:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then share it with the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.11,0:36:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the true nature of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.11,0:36:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,yes well this had to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.11,0:36:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 850
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.19,0:36:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which has never been explained
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.19,0:36:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world's literature
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.19,0:36:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that I know of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.19,0:36:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to say that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.19,0:36:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because somebody will email me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.19,0:36:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's confusion of nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.19,0:36:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with buddhahood
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.30,0:36:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so because there's nobody around to explain it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.30,0:36:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have to explain this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.59,0:36:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of negation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.59,0:36:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,huangpo
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.59,0:36:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,did we explain this last time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.07,0:36:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,huangpo is yes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.28,0:36:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ok well we'll just cover it again
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.28,0:36:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of negation then
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.28,0:36:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.28,0:36:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,negating the linear
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.28,0:36:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as a reality
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.28,0:36:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and not being attached to it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.28,0:36:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of negation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.32,0:36:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,will take you to the void
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.32,0:36:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which is consciousness level 850
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.38,0:36:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,now we found some interesting things
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.38,0:36:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,also never really
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.38,0:36:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,noticed before
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.38,0:36:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,these are characteristics of god
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.38,0:36:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but they calibrate different than
